<item>
            <title>[SOLR-17019] ZkCli should create subpaths when necessary</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-17019</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Certain zkCli.sh commands (clusterprop, put, putfile) use the zkClient.create() function.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, the clusterprop command is recommended to be used for setting the TLS property for SolrClouds that have not yet been started. Since Solr now supports creating chroots implicitly, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-7642&quot; title=&quot;Should launching Solr in cloud mode using a ZooKeeper chroot create the chroot znode if it doesn&amp;#39;t exist?&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-7642&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-7642&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, the zkCli.sh commands should work if the chroot doesn&apos;t exist yet.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is pretty easy to fix by changing the zkClient.create() to zkClient.makePath().&lt;/p&gt;</description>
